-- German Police Raid Turkish Charity That Sent Gaza Aid Shipment, NTV Says
-- Ercan Ersoy
-- 2010-07-13T10:18:45Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-13/german-police-raid-turkish-charity-that-sent-gaza-aid-shipment-ntv-says.html

          
          
             German police raided offices of the 
Turkey-based charity whose aid shipment to Gaza was raided by 
Israeli soldiers on May 31, killing nine activists, NTV 
television reported.  
 The raid targeted offices of the Humanitarian Relief 
Foundation, known as IHH, in three German cities, NTV said. 
Police carried out the raid on suspicion the organization has 
connections with terrorism, the broadcaster said.  
